solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    int minimizedStringLength(string s) {
        unordered_set<char> seen;
        for (char c : s) seen.insert(c);
        return seen.size();
    }
};```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Any character that appears at least once can be kept while all duplicates can be removed by repeatedly deleting adjacent duplicates. Thus the minimal length equals the count of distinct characters.

